## Adventuring Gear
This section describes items that have special rules or require further explanation.

***~~Abacus [SRD].~~*** [Removed due to being considered archaic in most cultures. Unless something like the tauren use them.]

***Acid [SRD].*** As an action, you can splash the contents of this vial onto a creature within 5 feet of you or throw the vial up to 20 feet, shattering it on impact. In either case, make a ranged attack against a creature or object, treating the acid as an improvised weapon. On a hit, the target takes 2d6 acid damage.

***Air Tank.*** [For diving, or other pressurized air uses, like being connected to a gas mask. Weight is for a full 80 cubic foot tank, which lasts ~1 hour. Empty tank weighs 25% less, so about 22.5 lbs.]

***~~Alchemist's Fire [SRD].~~*** ~~This sticky, adhesive fluid ignites when exposed to air. As an action, you can throw this flask up to 20 feet, shattering it on impact. Make a ranged attack against a creature or object, treating the alchemist's fire as an improvised weapon. On a hit, the target takes 1d4 fire damage at the start of each of its turns. A creature can end this damage by using its action to make a DC 10 Dexterity check to extinguish the flames.~~ [Removed due to not quite fitting in WoW setting. Will make a return as another item.]

***Animal Call.*** [Specific to each animal]

***Animal Collar.*** [For identifying owned animals]

***Animal Treats.*** []

***Antiplague.*** A creature that drinks this vial of liquid gains advantage on saving throws against disease for 1 hour. It confers no benefit to undead or constructs.

***Antitoxin [SRD].*** A creature that drinks this vial of liquid gains advantage on saving throws against poison for 1 hour. It confers no benefit to undead or constructs.

***Arcane Focus [SRD].*** An arcane focus is a special item—an orb, a crystal, a rod, a specially constructed staff, a wand-like length of wood, or some similar item— designed to channel the power of arcane spells. A ~~wizard~~ **mage or warlock** can use such an item as a spellcasting focus. **Additional Focuses:** Athame (ritual sacrifice knife), figurine (demonic figurine from WC3).

***Arclight Spanner.*** [Not sure if this needs an entry]

***Armor Maintenance Kit.*** [Whetstone equivalent]

***Army Knife.*** Popular among both goblins and gnomes, this compact device has many uses. Can be used as one of: Back scratcher, Block and tackle, crowbar, fishing rod, hammer, firestarter, magnifying glass, mirror, five-foot pole (alternate use of fishing rod), 25 feet silk rope and a grappling hook, saw, sewing needle, three kinds of signal whistles, shovel, a 1-person tent, whetstone, a whirly thing. Also cuts things as a small knife. Accessing any of these functions requires manipulating the device for 3 rounds.

***Ball Bearings [SRD.*** As an action, you can spill these tiny metal balls from their pouch to cover a level area 10 feet square. A creature moving across the covered area must succeed on a DC 10 Dexterity saving throw or fall prone. A creature moving through the area at half speed doesn't need to make the saving throw.

